Language name: BAKAIRI
Language number: 6856
Alternate names: Cura
Classification: South American, Macro-Carib
Comments: Bakairi is spoken in the Mato Grosso, Brazil. 
Wheatley, (1969, 1973) provides only sketchy information  
on the phonology. In particular it is not clear which 
vowels occur nasalized, but examples are cited with the 
nasalized vowels shown.

Sources: 

Wheatley, J. 1973. Pronouns and nominal elements in 
Bacairi discourse. Linguistics 104: 105-115.

Wheatley, J. 1969. Bakairi verb structure. Linguistics 47: 
80-100.